1️⃣ Escalation kya hai?
Matlab: Jab koi task, approval, ya issue apni original deadline me complete nahi hota, to wo upar ke level pe forward kar diya jata hai.
IAM / SailPoint me mostly Access Request, Approval, ya Certification workflow me hota hai.
Purpose: Delay ya inaction ko avoid karna aur ensure karna ki workflow complete ho.
✅ Simple:
“Escalation” = task ko upar ke manager / authority level pe bhejna, agar original owner action na le.

2️⃣ Escalation kaam kya karta hai

Approval me help karta hai:

Agar manager access request approve/reject nahi karta, to system automatically next level manager ya admin ko notify karta hai.

Access Certification / Review me help karta hai:

Agar reviewer access certify nahi karta, to workflow escalate hota hai higher authority ke paas.

Compliance aur SLA maintain karta hai:

Business aur audit ke liye ensure karta hai ki task time pe complete ho jaye.

3️⃣ Escalation ke andar kya hota hai

Task / Request: Jo action pending hai

Original Owner / Reviewer: Jisko kaam assign hua tha

Escalation Rule: Kab aur kis level pe escalate karna hai

Escalation Target: Upar ka manager, admin, ya authority

4️⃣ Example (SailPoint / IAM Workflow)

Scenario:

User X ne Finance role request kiya.

Manager Y ko approval mila.

3 din me Manager Y approve nahi karta.

Escalation Rule:

3 din me approval nahi mila → Finance Director ko notification send karo

Code / Pseudo Example:

AccessRequest request = context.getObjectByName(AccessRequest.class, "Finance Role Request");

if(request.isPending() && request.isOverdue()) {
    request.escalate("Finance Director");
    System.out.println("Request escalated to Finance Director");
}

Output:

Request escalated to Finance Director